!! Exceptions are quite strange word-forms. the ones that do not fit anywhere 
!! else. This file contains all enumerated word forms that cannot reasonably be
!! created from lexical data by regular inflection. Usually there should be next
!! to none exceptions, it's always better to have a paradigm that covers only
!! one or few words than an exception since these will not work nicely with e.g.
!! compounding scheme or possibly many end applications.

LEXICON EXCEPTIONS

!! negation verb has partial inflection:
!!β²§gt-norm: 
!!β²§ en:      ei+V+Neg+Act+Sg1
!!β²§ ΟΛlkΟΛΟΛ:   ei+V+Neg+Act+Imprt+Pl2
!!β²§ ΟΛlkΟΕΟΕt:  ei+V+Neg+Act+Imprt+Pl3
ei+V+Neg+Act+Sg1:en             VERB_FRONT_CLIT_OPT ;
ei+V+Neg+Act+Sg1+Foc/ka:enkΟΛ    VERB_FRONT_CLIT_OPT ;
ei+V+Neg+Act+Sg2:et             VERB_FRONT_CLIT_OPT ;
ei+V+Neg+Act+Sg2+Foc/ka:etkΟΛ    VERB_FRONT_CLIT_OPT ;
ei+V+Neg+Act+Sg3:ei             VERB_FRONT_CLIT_OPT ;
ei+V+Neg+Act+Sg3+Foc/ka:eikΟΛ    VERB_FRONT_CLIT_OPT ;
ei+V+Neg+Act+Pl1:emme           VERB_FRONT_CLIT_OPT ;
ei+V+Neg+Act+Pl1+Foc/ka:emmekΟΛ  VERB_FRONT_CLIT_OPT ;
ei+V+Neg+Act+Pl2:ette           VERB_FRONT_CLIT_OPT ;
ei+V+Neg+Act+Pl2+Foc/ka:ettekΟΛ  VERB_FRONT_CLIT_OPT ;
ei+V+Neg+Act+Pl3:eivΟΛt          VERB_FRONT_CLIT_OPT ;
ei+V+Neg+Act+Pl3+Foc/ka:eivΟΛtkΟΛ VERB_FRONT_CLIT_OPT ;
ei+V+Neg+Act+Imprt+Sg2:ΟΛlΟΛ                  VERB_FRONT_CLIT_OPT ;
ei+V+Neg+Act+Imprt+Sg2+Foc/ka:ΟΛlΟΛkΟΛ         VERB_FRONT_CLIT_OPT ;
ei+V+Neg+Act+Imprt+Sg3:ΟΛlkΟΕΟΕn               VERB_FRONT_CLIT_OPT ;
ei+V+Neg+Act+Imprt+Sg3+Foc/ka:ΟΛlkΟΕΟΕnkΟΛ      VERB_FRONT_CLIT_OPT ;
ei+V+Neg+Act+Imprt+Pl1:ΟΛlkΟΛΟΛmme             VERB_FRONT_CLIT_OPT ;
ei+V+Neg+Act+Imprt+Pl1+Foc/ka:ΟΛlkΟΛΟΛmmekΟΛ    VERB_FRONT_CLIT_OPT ;
ei+V+Neg+Act+Imprt+Pl2:ΟΛlkΟΛΟΛ                VERB_FRONT_CLIT_OPT ;
ei+V+Neg+Act+Imprt+Pl2+Foc/ka:ΟΛlkΟΛΟΛkΟΛ       VERB_FRONT_CLIT_OPT ;
ei+V+Neg+Act+Imprt+Pl3:ΟΛlkΟΕΟΕt               VERB_FRONT_CLIT_OPT ;
ei+V+Neg+Act+Imprt+Pl3+Foc/ka:ΟΛlkΟΕΟΕtkΟΛ      VERB_FRONT_CLIT_OPT ;

!! Some verbs only have few word-forms left:
